    @{ Name = 'mc_normals';    Flag = '--mc-normals' }          # Slice MC6 (GPU Isosurface Meshing SMOOTH FIELD-GRADIENT NORMALS, the 6th and FINAL MC slice — the finishing quality step that turns MC5's faceted sphere into a smooth one: the SAME MC1-MC4 sphere field (33³ corners -> 32³ cells, radius 12, iso 0, TotalTriangles=5240) is meshed by render/mc.h::MarchCellsInterp (the bit-exact mesh) then converted host-side by render/mc.h::BuildSmoothRenderMesh — IDENTICAL to MC5's BuildRenderMesh (position=vert/kSub, centered+scaled) EXCEPT the per-vertex normal is GradientNormal(vert,field): a central-difference SDF gradient (-∇f, the OUTWARD normal: ∇f points inward for the scalar=(radius-dist) field, so -∇f points away from the centre, the same outward convention MC5 used) at the vertex's grid neighbourhood (f at the 6 axis neighbours via SampleField, clamped) instead of MC5's flat per-face normal. POSITIONS + INDICES are byte-identical to MC5 (the MC4 bit-exact mesh — provenance unchanged); only the normal changes -> adjacent triangles share consistent vertex normals -> the sphere shades SMOOTH (Gouraud), no facets. Rendered lit + shadowed from the SAME fixed 3/4 camera + light through the EXISTING lit mesh pipeline (lit.vert + lit.frag, scene::MeshVertexLayout, FrameData UBO, sky + static-shadow + post — REUSED VERBATIM from MC5; NO new shader / RHI). Same FLOAT visresolve bar as MC5: a per-backend Metal-baked golden (Metal==Metal-golden DIFF 0.0000, deterministic two-run) + provenance + a documented cross-vendor smoke (~55-60 mean Vulkan-vs-Metal — the float baseline, NOT zero-diff). PROOFS: (1) provenance — the rendered mesh's vertex+index buffers == MarchCellsInterp ({tris:5240, verts:15720}); (2) determinism — two renders BYTE-IDENTICAL; (3) gradient-normal correctness — every gradient normal unit-length + outward-oriented (dot(N,vertexPos)>0 after centering, >90% of non-degenerate verts) AND the smooth normal set DIFFERS from the MC5 flat normals (the refineme