    @{ Name = 'gjk_settle';    Flag = '--gjk-settle' }          # Slice GJ4 (Deterministic General Convex-Hull Contacts THE HULL WORLD STEP — the new-physics beat, the 4th slice of FLAGSHIP #22: hf::sim::gjk. The convex::StepConvexWorld 5-pass shell with the ONLY swap being BoxSatStable -> the GJK/EPA HullContact narrowphase, so arbitrary convex polyhedra (tetra/octa/wedge) integrate, collide, and SETTLE — a tetra resting on its triangular FACE, physics the box-only SAT can't represent. APPENDS to gjk.h (GJ1-GJ3 + convex.h/fric.h/persist.h/fpx.h byte-frozen): FxHullInvInertiaBody (the diagonal box inverse inertia of the hull's bounding half-extents — exact for a cube hull == FxBoxInvInertiaBody, reuses convex::WorldInvInertia), HullContact (Gjk -> separated? empty : Epa -> a single-point convex::ContactManifold, normal=EPA normal, point=midpoint of the EPA witnesses, depth=EPA depth), HullWorld {parallel bodies/hulls}, StepHullWorld/StepHullWorldN (the 5-pass tick: predict-integrate+damping -> all-pairs i<j HullContact -> world Gauss-Seidel SolveManifoldImpulse -> POSITION de-pen -> orientation; angDamp is the single-point-manifold rest knob), HullStackMeasure/MeasureHullStack. A static floor box-hull (half-extent 4 — the frozen GJK stalls deep inside a larger box) + a dropped tetra + a dropped octa + a static box + a wedge is stepped K=240 ticks by shaders/hull_step.comp — ONE thread ([numthreads(1,1,1)]) runs the WHOLE StepHullWorldN copied VERBATIM (order-dependent -> single-thread) — GPU final body world memcmp'd BIT-EXACT vs the CPU gjk::StepHullWorldN. int64 (the GJK/EPA support + inertia fxdiv + FxDot/FxCross/FxRotate/quaternion products) -> hull_step.comp is VULKAN-SPIR-V-ONLY (DXC compiles int64; glslc cannot) -> NOT in hf_gen_msl; the Metal --gjk-settle runs the CPU StepHullWorldN (byte-identical by construction, the convex_step.comp/gjk_epa.comp split). The image golden is a PURE-INTEGER 2D side-view (XY) of the settled hull world (each hull's projected X