    @{ Name = 'ccd_lockstep';  Flag = '--ccd-lockstep' }         # Slice CD5 (Deterministic Integer CCD LOCKSTEP + ROLLBACK — THE NETCODE HEADLINE of FLAGSHIP #24: hf::sim::ccd, the BP5/GJ5/CX5/FR5/PS5 twin. PURE CPU — NO GPU compute, NO new shader, NO new RHI. CD1-CD4 built the time-of-impact primitive, the swept-AABB broadphase, the substepped CCD world step, and the bullet-wall beat. CD5 proves the whole CCD-driven hull sim is LOCKSTEP- and ROLLBACK-replayable: two peers fed only an input-command stream re-derive the entire world — INCLUDING the per-substep time-of-impact — byte-identical, and a rollback re-sims from a snapshot bit-for-bit. THE HEADLINE: the TOI is re-derived each substep from the current positions/velocities, so two peers re-compute the SAME impact times -> the lockstep holds THROUGH the swept continuous solve. Mainstream float engines DISABLE CCD in lockstep netcode (non-deterministic root-finding); HF is bit-identical + replayable. APPENDS to ccd.h (CD1-CD4 + broad.h/gjk.h/convex.h/fpx.h/fric.h/persist.h/grain.h byte-frozen; reuses the frozen gjk:: command/snapshot/equality machinery): SimCcdTick (= gjk::ApplyHullCommands + StepHullWorldCCD), RunCcdLockstep (two peers from world0 over the SAME stream -> the converged authority world + authority==replica byte-equality), RunCcdRollback (advance to rollbackAt, SnapshotHull, speculatively mispredict, RestoreHull, re-sim the correct stream; corrected==authority + mispredict-diverged flags). BOTH the Vulkan --ccd-lockstep-shot AND the Metal --ccd-lockstep run the IDENTICAL pure-CPU harness over the CD4 bullet-wall scene + a fixed command stream (a launch-impulse fires the projectile, the wall arrests it, a later command perturbs a slow drop) -> the converged authority-world golden is bit-identical cross-backend BY CONSTRUCTION (strict zero-differing-pixel). PROOFS: (1) 'ccd-lockstep: {bodies:<N>, ticks:<K>, commands:<C>} authority==replica BIT-IDENTICAL'; (2) 'ccd-lockstep determinism: two runs BYTE