    @{ Name = 'ccd_bullet';    Flag = '--ccd-bullet' }           # Slice CD4 (Deterministic Integer CCD A BULLET THROUGH A THIN WALL STOPS — THE HEADLINE BEAT of FLAGSHIP #24: hf::sim::ccd. CD1-CD3 built the time-of-impact primitive, the swept-AABB broadphase, and the substepped CCD world step. CD4 is the money-shot DEMONSTRATION: a fast projectile fired at a thin static wall is ARRESTED at the wall's near face — the per-tick travel is MANY times the wall thickness, so a DISCRETE solver (broad::StepHullWorldBP) tunnels it straight through, while the CCD step (StepHullWorldCCD) stops it exactly at impact, deterministically and bit-identically CPU/Vulkan/Metal. REUSES CD3's StepHullWorldCCD + ccd_step.comp ENTIRELY — adds ONLY the dedicated bullet-wall SCENE + the impact measurement + the discrete control. APPENDS to ccd.h (CD1-CD3 + broad.h/gjk.h/convex.h/fpx.h/fric.h/persist.h/grain.h byte-frozen): MakeBulletWallScene (a thin static wall + a fast +X projectile whose |vel|*dt is ~50x the wall thickness, + a floor + slow drops; FIXED indices 0=projectile/1=wall/2-3=drops/4=floor), MakeBulletWallConfig (the pure-horizontal-shot CcdStepConfig), BulletMeasure/MeasureBullet (is the projectile past the wall's far face?) + StepBulletImpactTick (the arrest tick). The SAME scene is stepped K ticks by shaders/ccd_step.comp (CD3's shader REUSED VERBATIM — NO new shader; the bullet-wall is just a different INPUT WORLD to the same dispatch), chunked 1 tick/dispatch (TDR-safe). GPU CCD final body world memcmp'd BIT-EXACT vs the CPU ccd::StepHullWorldCCDN AND tunneled=false. int64 -> ccd_step.comp is Vulkan-only (Metal --ccd-bullet runs the CPU StepHullWorldCCDN, byte-identical by construction). The image golden is a PURE-INTEGER 2D side-view (XY) of the CCD final world (the projectile ARRESTED at the wall, the slow drops settled) -> identical both backends by construction (the strict zero-differing-pixel bar). PROOFS: (1) 'ccd-bullet: {tunneled:false, impactTick:<T>} GPU==CPU BIT-