    @{ Name = 'ccd_step';      Flag = '--ccd-step' }             # Slice CD3 (Deterministic Integer CCD THE SUBSTEPPED CCD WORLD STEP — THE MECHANISM BEAT of FLAGSHIP #24: hf::sim::ccd. CD1 built the time-of-impact PRIMITIVE (ConservativeAdvance); CD2 built the swept-AABB BROADPHASE (BuildSweptBroadphasePairs). CD3 ASSEMBLES them into a SUBSTEPPED CCD world step: each tick, sweep-broadphase the candidate pairs, compute each pair's TOI, advance ALL bodies to the EARLIEST impact, resolve that contact via the FROZEN solver, then consume the remaining dt and repeat — so a FAST body STOPS at the first thing it would hit instead of tunneling through it in one big tick. APPENDS to ccd.h (CD1+CD2 + broad.h/gjk.h/convex.h/fpx.h/fric.h/persist.h/grain.h byte-frozen): CcdStepConfig (= broad::BroadStepConfig + maxSubsteps), ResolveTouchingPairCCD (the at-TOI resolve over one pair, reusing the broad::StepHullWorldBP solve + de-pen passes VERBATIM), StepHullWorldCCD/StepHullWorldCCDN (the bounded substep loop: swept broadphase -> per-pair ConservativeAdvance -> the GLOBAL-MIN TOI [lowest-pair-index tie] -> integrate ALL dynamic bodies by minToi [or the full remainingDt if no hit] + damping -> resolve the touching pairs -> remainingDt -= minToi, loop), CcdMeasure/MeasureCcd. A MODERATE scene (a FAST mover aimed at a thin static wall + a few slow settling hulls) is stepped K ticks by shaders/ccd_step.comp — ONE thread ([numthreads(1,1,1)]) runs the WHOLE StepHullWorldCCDN copied VERBATIM (the all-pairs swept-AABB gate reproduces the CPU grid candidate set — a non-swept-overlapping pair is a ConservativeAdvance no-op; the min-TOI is order-invariant; the resolve iterates the HIT pairs in (i,j)-ascending order), CHUNKED at 1 TICK/DISPATCH from the start (the HEAVIEST single-thread dispatch in the suite; a 1-tick dispatch is provably << the ~2s TDR watchdog, TDR-safe by construction) with a barrier between (bit-identical to one big dispatch) — GPU final body world memcmp'd BIT-EXACT vs