    @{ Name = 'ccd_swept';     Flag = '--ccd-swept' }            # Slice CD2 (Deterministic Integer CCD THE SWEPT-AABB BROADPHASE — the 2nd slice of FLAGSHIP #24: hf::sim::ccd. Each body's broadphase box is the UNION of its world AABB at the tick start and at the integrated end pose — the SWEPT AABB — so a FAST mover's sweep overlaps obstacles the discrete (instantaneous-AABB) broadphase MISSES (tunneling). APPENDS to ccd.h (CD1 + broad.h/gjk.h/convex.h/fpx.h/fric.h/persist.h/grain.h byte-frozen): SweptHullAabb (broad::BuildHullAabb at the start pose UNION at the integrated end pose, bodyEnd = a COPY advanced by dt via fpx::IntegrateBodyFull ZERO gravity — statics don't move so their swept box == instantaneous), BuildSweptBroadphasePairs (precompute the swept AABBs -> broad::MakeBodyGrid/BuildBodyCellTable over the AABB-centre proxies -> the BP2 pure-int32 count->scan->emit keyed on the explicit lo/hi swept AABBs), BuildDiscreteBroadphasePairs (the same generator over the INSTANTANEOUS AABBs), SweptPairsSupersetOfDiscrete (TRUE iff swept ⊇ discrete; reports M = swept pairs the discrete set misses), SweptPairMeasure/MeasureSweptPairs. The swept-AABB precompute (integrate + 2x BuildHullAabb + union — the int64 part) is HOST-side; the int32 lo/hi AABBs feed THREE pure-int32 GPU passes ccd_swept_count.comp (ONE thread/body i scans its 3x3x3 stencil over the AABB-centre cell table, counts j>i with the six-compare AabbOverlap over lo/hi) -> ccd_swept_scan.comp (SINGLE-THREAD exclusive prefix-sum -> perBodyOffset) -> ccd_swept_emit.comp (SINGLE-THREAD ascending-body scatter of fpx::FxPair{i,j}, the per-i emit-order DET-CRUX). ALL PURE INT32 (NO int64/fxmul/sqrt) so these MSL-generate NATIVELY and Metal --ccd-swept dispatches the GPU passes directly (a TRUE GPU pass on BOTH backends, the broad_pair_* tier). ReadBuffer reads perBodyOffset + pairsOut PROVEN BIT-EXACT vs the CPU ccd::BuildSweptBroadphasePairs (memcmp, NO tol). PROOFS (fail loudly): (1) 'ccd-swept: {bodies:<N>,