    @{ Name = 'nav_distfield'; Flag = '--nav-distance' }         # Slice NAV2 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh WALKABLE FILTER + INTEGER CHAMFER DISTANCE FIELD, the 2nd slice of FLAGSHIP #7 — extend the NAV1 heightfield: filter which spans are WALKABLE (integer clearance-above >= walkableHeight + the 4-neighbour abs(surfaceY) max-step/climb connectivity test) into a per-column walkable surface, then build an INTEGER two-pass chamfer DISTANCE FIELD over the walkable cells (cardinal weight 2 / diagonal weight 3, NO sqrt, NO int64; seed non-walkable+border=0/walkable=INF, forward TL->BR then backward BR->TL min-sweep, only traversing walkable+connected neighbours -> geodesic) that NAV3's watershed regions consume. Both stages PURE INT32 -> strict zero-differing-pixel cross-backend (the NAV1 integer bar). The NAV1 showcase heightfield (ground plane + box-step + ramp) is rasterized + per-column MERGED on the host, then two pure-INT32 compute passes: nav_filter.comp (ONE thread per column: walk the merged spans, mark walkable -> gWalkable[col]+gSurfaceY[col]) -> (compute->compute barrier) -> nav_distance.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] single-thread two-pass chamfer -> gDist[], the nav_raster_scan/mc_scan serial mirror); FilterWalkableSpans/IsConnected/BuildDistanceField copied VERBATIM from engine/nav/navmesh.h. UNLIKE FPX1''s int64 fxmul integrator (Vulkan-only -> CPU on Metal), these are PURE INT32 (no int64 in any shader), so the shaders MSL-generate NATIVELY and Metal DISPATCHES THE GPU passes directly. ReadBuffer reads gWalkable + gDist, PROVEN BIT-EXACT vs the CPU navmesh.h::FilterWalkableSpans+BuildDistanceField reference (full-buffer memcmp, NO tolerance), enabled=false -> walkable 0 / dist 0 no-op, two runs byte-identical; the image golden is a top-down heat-ramp distance-field viz — identical both backends by construction (PURE INTEGER); pure compute over Storage SSBOs + a compute->compute barrier + ReadBuffer — NO watershed regions (NAV3), NO new RHI; NAV1''s nav_raster pipeline + nav_spans golden + the FLOAT engine/physics/ + engine/sim/fpx.h UNTOUCHED (nav is additive + parallel; navmesh.h #includes fpx.h read-only for FloorDiv))
    @{ Name = 'nav_spans';     Flag = '--nav-raster' }          # Slice NAV1 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh INTEGER HEIGHTFIELD SPAN RASTERIZATION, the BEACHHEAD of FLAGSHIP #7 — rasterize host-snapped voxel triangles into a per-column SOLID-SPAN heightfield, bit-exact CPU<->Vulkan<->Metal. A deterministic showcase mesh (ground plane + a raised box-step + a ramp) is meshed by three pure-INT32 compute passes (the MC3 count->scan->emit on voxel columns): nav_raster_count.comp (ONE thread per column (cx,cz): colCount[col]=#triangles whose XZ projection covers the column-center) -> (compute->compute barrier) -> nav_raster_scan.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] single-thread exclusive prefix-sum -> colOffset) -> (barrier) -> nav_raster_emit.comp (ONE thread per column emits each covering tri's integer y-span into gSpans at its DISJOINT range -> race-free, NO atomics); TriColumnAabb + PointInTriXZ (three integer edge functions) + TriYSpan copied VERBATIM from engine/nav/navmesh.h. UNLIKE FPX1''s int64 fxmul integrator (Vulkan-only -> CPU on Metal), the rasterizer is PURE INT32 (no int64 in any shader), so the shaders MSL-generate NATIVELY and Metal DISPATCHES THE GPU passes directly. ReadBuffer reads gSpans + gColOffset, PROVEN BIT-EXACT vs the CPU navmesh.h::RasterizeTriangleSpans reference (full-buffer memcmp, NO tolerance), enabled=false -> zero spans no-op, two runs byte-identical; the image golden is a top-down per-column span-count viz — identical both backends by construction (PURE INTEGER); pure compute over Storage SSBOs + compute->compute barriers + ReadBuffer — NO walkable filter (NAV2+), NO new RHI; the FLOAT engine/physics/ + engine/sim/fpx.h UNTOUCHED (nav is additive + parallel; navmesh.h #includes fpx.h read-only for FloorDiv))
    @{ Name = 'nav_regions';   Flag = '--nav-region' }          # Slice NAV3 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh INTEGER WATERSHED REGION GENERATION, the 3rd slice + MAKE-OR-BREAK of FLAGSHIP #7 — partition the NAV2 walkable distance field into REGIONS (connected walkable basins, distinct deterministic ids) via an INTEGER WATERSHED. The make-or-break: a naive watershed''s flood wavefront depends on visitation order; NAV3 LOCKS a level-descending, fixed-scan-order, lowest-region-id-tie-break flood run SINGLE-THREAD ([numthreads(1,1,1)]) so the GPU is bit-exact to the CPU reference by construction. The NAV1 showcase heightfield (ground plane + box-step + ramp) is rasterized + per-column MERGED on the host, then three pure-INT32 compute passes: nav_filter.comp (-> gWalkable[]+gSurfaceY[]) -> (barrier) -> nav_distance.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] two-pass chamfer -> gDist[]) -> (barrier) -> nav_region.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] single-thread level-descending watershed: for level=maxDist..1 GROW existing regions into this level by lowest-region-id among connected neighbours in ascending cellId until stable, then SEED + grow any still-unassigned cell -> gRegion[], 0=none, ids dense from 1); MaxDistOf/BuildRegions/IsConnected copied VERBATIM from engine/nav/navmesh.h. UNLIKE FPX1''s int64 fxmul integrator (Vulkan-only -> CPU on Metal), the watershed is PURE INT32 (no int64 in any shader), so the shader MSL-generates NATIVELY and Metal DISPATCHES THE GPU pass directly. ReadBuffer reads gRegion, PROVEN BIT-EXACT vs the CPU navmesh.h::BuildRegions reference (full-buffer memcmp, NO tolerance), enabled=false -> region 0 no-op, two runs byte-identical; the image golden is a top-down hash-colored region-partition viz (>=2 regions, each a single 4-connected component) — identical both backends by construction (PURE INTEGER); pure compute over Storage SSBOs + compute->compute barriers + ReadBuffer — NO region merge/contour (NAV4+), NO new RHI; NAV1''s nav_raster + nav_spans golden + NAV2''s nav