    @{ Name = 'nav_polymesh';  Flag = '--nav-polymesh' }        # Slice NAV4 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh CONTOUR TRACE + INTEGER POLYGONIZATION, the 4th slice of FLAGSHIP #7 — turn the NAV3 region partition into a POLYGON MESH: trace each region's boundary into an integer CONTOUR, simplify it (integer Douglas-Peucker, perpendicular-distance-squared vs maxError^2, NO sqrt), triangulate it (ear-clip, clip the LOWEST-index valid ear via integer Cross2 orientation + point-in-triangle) into convex polys (triangles) + per-edge cross-poly ADJACENCY — the graph NAV5''s A* runs over. PURE INT32 (corner coords <=32 for the 32x32 showcase, the documented overflow bound; NO int64, NO float) -> strict zero-differing-pixel cross-backend (the NAV1-NAV3 integer bar). The NAV1-NAV3 pipeline (rasterize+merge+filter+distance+regions) runs exactly as --nav-region, then two NEW pure-INT32 single-thread compute passes: nav_contour.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] trace each region boundary lowest-cellId-start + fixed wall-follow turn order, then Douglas-Peucker simplify -> gContourVerts + per-region offsets/counts) -> (compute->compute barrier) -> nav_polygonize.comp ([numthreads(1,1,1)] ear-clip triangulate + per-edge adjacency -> gPolys (8 uints/poly: idx[3], nbr[3], region, pad) + per-region offsets/counts); TraceContours/SimplifyContour/BuildPolyMesh copied VERBATIM from engine/nav/navmesh.h. UNLIKE FPX1''s int64 fxmul integrator (Vulkan-only -> CPU on Metal), these are PURE INT32 (no int64 in any shader), so the shaders MSL-generate NATIVELY and Metal DISPATCHES THE GPU passes directly. ReadBuffer reads gContourVerts + gPolys, PROVEN BIT-EXACT vs the CPU navmesh.h::TraceContours+SimplifyContour+BuildPolyMesh reference (full-buffer memcmp, NO tolerance — the make-or-break), enabled=false -> 0 contours / 0 polys no-op, two runs byte-identical; the image golden draws the region fills (faint) + simplified contour edges (bright) + triangulated poly edges (per-region hashColor) — identical both backends by construction (PURE INTEGER); pure compute over Storage SSBOs + compute->compute barriers + ReadBuffer — NO convex-poly MERGING beyond triangles / detail mesh (deferred), NO A* (NAV5), NO new RHI; NAV1''s nav_raster + nav_spans golden + NAV2''s nav_filter/nav_distance + nav_distfield golden + NAV3''s nav_region + nav_regions golden + the FLOAT engine/physics/ + engine/sim/fpx.h UNTOUCHED (nav is additive + parallel; navmesh.h #includes fpx.h read-only for FloorDiv))
    @{ Name = 'nav_path';      Flag = '--nav-path' }          # Slice NAV5 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh INTEGER A* PATHFINDING, the 5th slice + HEADLINE of FLAGSHIP #7 — run integer A* (Manhattan cost+heuristic over poly centroids, lowest-id tie-break) over the NAV4 poly adjacency graph (nav_astar.comp, [numthreads(1,1,1)] single-thread, copied VERBATIM from engine/nav/navmesh.h::ConnectedComponents/SelectStartGoal/FindPath) -> a deterministic CORRIDOR (poly-id sequence start->goal) + total cost; GPU==CPU corridor+cost+start/goal bit-exact (the make-or-break), PURE INT32 (NO int64) -> MSL-gens natively + Metal dispatches the GPU pass directly, strict zero-differing-pixel cross-backend; the golden draws the navmesh (faint) + the corridor polyline (bright, through poly centroids, start green/goal red); NO new RHI; NAV1-NAV4 + the FLOAT engine/physics/ + engine/sim/fpx.h UNTOUCHED)
    @{ Name = 'nav_render';    Flag = '--nav-render' }        # Slice NAV6 (Deterministic GPU Navmesh LIT 3D RENDER CAPSTONE, the 6th + FINAL slice COMPLETING FLAGSHIP #7 — render the bit-exact integer navmesh + A* corridor as a lit 3D scene. Runs the deterministic NAV1-NAV5 pipeline (CPU, the SAME 32x32 showcase) to a polymesh + corridor, converts the integer polys + corridor to FLOAT host-side via engine/nav/navmesh.h::NavVertToWorld/PolyMeshToRenderMesh/PathToWorldPolyline (the ONE render-only host float crossing; NAV1-NAV5 build/pathfind stay integer + byte-identical), and renders a lit ground (the EXISTING lit-mesh pipeline) + the walkable navmesh polys as a TRANSLUCENT per-region overlay (the EXISTING transparent/glass pass) + the A* corridor as a bright debug LINE + start/goal markers (the EXISTING debug-line pass) over sky + static-shadow + post, from a fixed 3/4 camera + light — REUSED VERBATIM, NO new shader/RHI. FLOAT visresolve-bar (like FPX6/MC5): the SAME 32x32 navmesh runs on BOTH backends so the CPU geometry is byte-identical, but the final raster/shade is float, so the golden is Metal-baked + the gate is Metal-determinism (two renders BYTE-IDENTICAL) + provenance (the rendered mesh + line derive from the bit-exact integer NAV4 polys + NAV5 corridor); the Vulkan-vs-Metal cross-vendor delta is the documented float baseline (~55-60 mean, NOT zero). PROOFS: (1) 'nav-render: {regions:<R>, polys:<P>, corridor:<L>, shaded:<S>} (integer navmesh -> lit 3D render)'; (2) two renders BYTE-IDENTICAL; (3) 'nav-render coverage: <S> shaded (coherent navmesh + path)' (shaded>0, non-uniform); (4) 'nav-render empty: base only (no-op)' (zero polys -> lit ground only). NO new RHI; NAV1-NAV5 + their goldens + shaders UNCHANGED (NAV6 is purely additive — render-only float helpers + a new showcase), the FLOAT engine/physics/ + engine/sim/fpx.h UNTOUCHED. Completes the 6-slice deterministic-navmesh-and-pathfinding flagship)
    @{ Name = 'mt';            Flag = '--mt' }                   # Slice AU (multithreaded recording; Metal N=4 parallel encoder)
